  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Andhra Bank has merged with the Union Bank of India. For updated services and procedures, you should refer to Union Bank's policies.\n\nHowever, online application for internet banking typically involves:\n\n1. **Website Access**: Visit the Union Bank of India website (since Andhra Bank has merged with Union Bank of India).\n2. **Register Online**: Look for the 'Register for Internet Banking' option.\n3. **Submit Details**: Fill in the required details, such as your account number, registered mobile number, and other necessary information.\n4. **Password Generation/OTP Verification**: You may need to generate a password through an OTP (One-Time Password) sent to your registered mobile number or email.\n5. **Activation**: Depending on the bank\u2019s policies, you might need to activate your internet banking through an activation link sent to your email or by visiting the branch to submit some documents.\n\nBefore proceeding, it is always best to contact the bank directly or visit their official website for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
